drama graduate student showcase the ballad of betsy paradise arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe calendar drama graduate student showcase the ballad of betsy paradise thursday march 1 2012 8 00pm nitery theater in the old union tickets $5 general admisssion at http drama stanford edu please note that this performance space does not accommodate late seating march 1 & 2 at 8pm & 10pm written by dan poston directed by joy brooke fairfield the ballad of betsy paradise is a play within a play within a dream of a play within a treehouse nestled in the towering redwood forest eleven year old jellia oceanblue was born and raised in northern california with as much opportunity as her mother could afford and grandmother could imagine but it's still not enough hungry for the exciting future of social revolution that she reads about on the internet jellia invites a flashy social theorist from new york city to stay in her treehouse for one event filled week but is the glamorous betsy paradise all that she seems with one eye turned to the past and one searching into the future this play looks at how generations construct and deconstruct each others myths and aspirations sponsored by department of drama click for more information home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
